---

This project interacts with the following external standards, specifications,
and data formats. No source code from these is bundled; the project reads
documented public interfaces / file formats only.

  * Claude Code statusLine specification
    stdin JSON shape: context_window.{context_window_size, used_percentage,
    current_usage, total_input_tokens}, rate_limits.{five_hour, seven_day}
    https://code.claude.com/docs/en/statusline

  * Claude Desktop (Cowork / local agent mode) session audit log format
    Per-session audit.jsonl and local_<sessionId>.json metadata files.

  * Model Context Protocol (MCP)
    https://modelcontextprotocol.io/

---

Runtime dependencies:

  * Python "mcp" SDK (Model Context Protocol Python SDK)
    Installed via pip (see mcp-server/requirements.txt); not bundled.
    https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/python-sdk

  * jq — command-line JSON processor (used by the CLI recipe and the
    statusLine wrapper). MIT License. Not bundled.
    https://github.com/jqlang/jq

Optional, not required:

  * ccstatusline — a third-party Claude Code status line renderer. The
    bundled statusline-wrapper.sh uses it as the default display command if
    present, and falls back to a dump-only mode if it is not installed.
    See its own repository for its license and terms.

These tools are not statically linked or repackaged by this project.
